%S A395773 1,1,3,2,5,3,8,4,9,5,12,6,14,8,15,8,16,9,18,10,24,12,22,12,25,14,27,
%T A395773 16,30,15,30,16,36,16,40,18,38,18,42,20,42,24,44,24,45,22,46,24,56,25,
%U A395773 48,28,52,27,60,32,54,30,60,30,60,30,72,32,70,36,68,32,66,40
%N A395773 The twisted Euler phi-function for the Dirichlet character kronecker(-15,.) mod 15.
%C A395773 We have h(-15*n^2), the class number of the order of Z[(1+sqrt(-15))/2] with discriminant -15*n^2, is equal to 2*a(n).
%C A395773 In general, let d < 0 be a fundamental discriminant and n be a positive integer such that d*n^2 < -4, then h(d*n^2) = L(0,kronecker(d,.)) * n * Product_{p|n, p prime} (1 - kronecker(d,p)/p). This is a combination of Theorem 7.24 in "Primes of the form x^2+ny^2" by Cox and the Dirichlet class number formula. Here L(0,kronecker(-15,.)) = 2.
%D A395773 D. A. Cox, Primes of the form x^2+ny^2, Wiley, New York, 1989, p. 146.
%F A395773 Multiplicative with a(3^e) = 3^e, a(5^e) = 5^e, a(p^e) = p^(e-1)*(p-1) if p == 1, 2, 4, 8 (mod 15) and a(p^e) = p^(e-1)*(p+1) if p == 7, 11, 13, 14 (mod 15).
%e A395773 Given L(0,kronecker(-15,.)) = 2, we have: h(-15*1^2) = 2*a(1) = 2, h(-15*2^2) = 2*a(2) = 2, h(-15*3^2) = 2*a(3) = 6, h(-15*4^2) = 2*a(4) = 4, ...
%o A395773 (PARI) a(n,{d=-15}) = my(f=factor(n)[,1]~, w=#f); n * prod(i=1, w, 1 - kronecker(d,f[i])/f[i])
%Y A395773 A316569 is the corresponding Dirichlet character.
%Y A395773 Cf. for fundamental discriminants -3..-24: A227128, A395768, A395771, A395769, A395772, this sequence, A395774, A395775, A395776, A395777.
%K A395773 nonn,easy,mult,new
%O A395773 1,3
